Now I have the full picture. The deobfuscated core loop is:

```javascript
for (const key of Object.keys(source)) {
    isObject(target[key]) && isObject(source[key])
        ? assign(target[key], source[key])          // recursive merge into target[key]
        : target[key] = source[key];
}
```

When `key === '__proto__'`, `target['__proto__']` resolves to `Object.prototype`, so the recursive call becomes `assign(Object.prototype, source['__proto__'])` — classic prototype pollution.

